from\": 6120, \"to\": 6128}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400m freestyle\", \"from\": 6158, \"to\": 6176}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was her real coming out party, though, as she showed off a variety of strokes in winning both the 200m (in an Olympic record 2:06.56) and 400m individual medleys, which are essentially the all-around competition for swimmers.\", \"from\": 6187, \"to\": 6417, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"party\", \"from\": 6216, \"to\": 6221}, {\"ngram\": \"a variety\", \"from\": 6249, \"to\": 6258}, {\"ngram\": \"strokes\", \"from\": 6262, \"to\": 6269}, {\"ngram\": \"both the 200m\", \"from\": 6281, \"to\": 6294}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic record 2:06.56\", \"from\": 6299, \"to\": 6324}, {\"ngram\": \"400m individual medleys\", \"from\": 6330, \"to\": 6353}, {\"ngram\": \"the all-around competition\", \"from\": 6377, \"to\": 6403}, {\"ngram\": \"swimmers\", \"from\": 6408, \"to\": 6416}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She beat Olympic legend Katie Ledecky and finished just behind Ariarne Titmus in the 400m freestyle, then shook it off by winning the 200m butterfly in Olympic record time over American Regan Smith, who won two golds and three silvers herself.\", \"from\": 6418, \"to\": 6661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6442, \"end\": 6455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}, {\"begin\": 6595, \"end\": 6603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999935607775, \"rank\": 4.411758285177357e-09, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 6604, \"end\": 6615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1633114788419781e-60, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"from\": 6481, \"to\": 6495}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400m freestyle\", \"from\": 6499, \"to\": 6517}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200m butterfly\", \"from\": 6548, \"to\": 6566}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic record time\", \"from\": 6570, \"to\": 6589}, {\"ngram\": \"two golds\", \"from\": 6625, \"to\": 6634}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh comes from an athletic family.\", \"from\": 6663, \"to\": 6702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6663, \"end\": 6671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1300675217439565e-17, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an athletic family\", \"from\": 6683, \"to\": 6701}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her mom Jill Horstead represented Team Canada in the 1984 Olympics, and her sister Brooke is a pairs figure skater that has a real shot to make the 2026 Games in Milan.\", \"from\": 6703, \"to\": 6871, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6865, \"end\": 6870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A.C._Milan\", \"score\": 0.9999987672607271, \"rank\": 1.2327407970381048e-06, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A.C._Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A.C._Milan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her mom\", \"from\": 6703, \"to\": 6710}, {\"ngram\": \"Jill Horstead\", \"from\": 6711, \"to\": 6724}, {\"ngram\": \"Team Canada\", \"from\": 6737, \"to\": 6748}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1984 Olympics\", \"from\": 6752, \"to\": 6769}, {\"ngram\": \"her sister\", \"from\": 6775, \"to\": 6785}, {\"ngram\": \"Brooke\", \"from\": 6786, \"to\": 6792}, {\"ngram\": \"a pairs figure skater\", \"from\": 6796, \"to\": 6817}, {\"ngram\": \"a real shot\", \"from\": 6827, \"to\": 6838}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2026 Games\", \"from\": 6847, \"to\": 6861}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If McIntosh could be this good at so young an age, it's scary to think what she might accomplish in 2028 when the Games are played on her home continent.\", \"from\": 6873, \"to\": 7026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6876, \"end\": 6884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1300675217439565e-17, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"so young an age\", \"from\": 6907, \"to\": 6922}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 6983, \"to\": 6992}, {\"ngram\": \"her home continent\", \"from\": 7007, \"to\": 7025}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being selected as a flagbearer for the Closing Ceremony is an honor typically bestowed upon a veteran near the end of their career, but after McIntosh's performance in Paris, there really was no other choice.\", \"from\": 7027, \"to\": 7235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7169, \"end\": 7177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1300675217439565e-17, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 7195, \"end\": 7200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1166910632794817e-31, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a flagbearer\", \"from\": 7045,